  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version 1.8.17-stable-8bbe7207`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nGeth powers through consensus failures and never looks back.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nGeth is able to sync the Ropsten testnet through the consensus failure and catch up to the lead canonical block. Unfortunately, when we enable the geth miner and connect through a stratum pool, we immediately fall back in the Ropsten chain. We continue to mine blocks and fall further back in the chain, and eventually get an out of memory error and the client dies.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nSee Ropsten.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nsee gist: https://gist.github.com/atlanticcrypto/a078b3a9be7f2054824463b25056496b\r\n````\r\n",
